Credit Ratings
DAYTON POWER  LIGHT Co. (Dayton, Ohio) -- Moody's
Investors Service Inc. raised the credit ratings of this
utility, the principal subsidiary of DPL Inc. The move, which
affects about $855 million of long-term debt, reflects
regulatory approval of rate increases covering the utility's
share of the operating and capital costs for the Zimmer
Station. Ratings on Dayton PL's first mortgage bonds and
secured pollution control issues were raised to single-A-2
from single-A-3; debentures and unsecured pollution control
issues were raised to single-A-3 from Baa-1; and preferred
stock was raised to single-A-2 from Baa-1. The company's
rating for short-term debt was raised to Prime-1 from
Prime-2.